### Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Can I use PigeonLab for my university research?**
A: Yes. Any researcher at any university or college, anywhere in the world,
can use PigeonLab completely free. This includes undergraduate, graduate,
postdoctoral, and faculty research.

**Q: What about grant-funded research?**
A: Totally fine. Research funded by NIH, NSF, ERC, UKRI, or any other grant
agency is fully permitted. The funding source doesn't matter — if you're
doing research, you can use it.

**Q: Can I publish papers using data analyzed by PigeonLab?**
A: Yes. Publishing research results is permitted and encouraged. Please cite
PigeonLab in your publications.

**Q: Can I share PigeonLab with a collaborator at another university?**
A: Yes. You can share the Software with any academic collaborator. They get
the same rights under this license.

**Q: Can I modify PigeonLab and share my version with other labs?**
A: Yes, as long as your modified version keeps this same license and is not
sold or commercialized.

**Q: Can I use PigeonLab in a course I teach?**
A: Yes. Educational use is fully permitted, including distributing it to
students.

**Q: Can I use it for research on animals other than pigeons?**
A: Yes. The license doesn't restrict what species you study. If you adapt
the Software for other research, that's fine under this license.

**Q: Can a company use PigeonLab internally?**
A: No, not without a separate commercial license. Internal corporate use is
considered commercial use, even if the Software itself is not being resold.

**Q: Can I build a paid SaaS product using PigeonLab?**
A: No. This is explicitly prohibited without a commercial license.

**Q: Can I fork PigeonLab and sell my version?**
A: No. Derivative works must use this same non-commercial license.

**Q: What if a company sponsors my academic research and I use PigeonLab?**
A: If you are a researcher at an academic institution and the work is
academic research (even if industry-sponsored), you may use PigeonLab. If
the company itself is running PigeonLab on their own systems for their own
purposes, they need a commercial license.

**Q: What if I'm a nonprofit animal research organization?**
A: Non-profit research organizations may use PigeonLab freely. If your
organization generates revenue from services that incorporate PigeonLab,
please contact us to discuss licensing.

**Q: Can a zoo or wildlife sanctuary use it?**
A: Yes, as long as they are not selling PigeonLab or offering it as a
paid service. Internal research and animal welfare use at non-commercial
organizations is permitted.
